message: Hello! To succeed in this game, remember these key rules: 1. Use the 'vial' tool for solid ingredients, it creates 'extracted' liquids. 2. Use the 'filter' tool for liquid and gas ingredients, it creates 'filtered' liquids. Both tools will raise an ingredient's value from 0 to 30. 3. The most critical rule: Only combine *two* items at a time. If an item is already a blend of two components, combining it with a third component (even if it's only one item from your inventory) will result in a negative value item. 4. When combining, try to match features: combine 'magical' items with other 'magical' items, and 'mundane' items with other 'mundane' items. Combining two 'processed' items (extracted or filtered) of the same type and value (30+30) will result in a 60-value item. Good luck!

message: To reach 100 points: Use the ğŸ§ª vial on solid ingredients to get 'liquid, extracted' items (value 30). Use the ğŸ§« filter on raw liquid or gas ingredients to get 'liquid, filtered' items (value 30). Avoid filtering items that are already 'extracted' as this creates 'poorly-filtered' items and reduces value. The key to 100 points is to combine exactly two liquid items: one magical and one mundane. The highest value combinations are either an 'extracted magical liquid' with an 'extracted mundane liquid', OR an 'extracted liquid' (magical or mundane) with a 'filtered liquid' (opposite type, i.e., mundane if the other is magical, or vice-versa).

message: To reach 100 points, the goal is to combine a magical *processed* liquid with a mundane *processed* liquid. Use the 'vial' tool on all solid ingredients (magical and mundane) to create 'extracted' liquids. Use the 'filter' tool on all gas ingredients (magical and mundane) to create 'filtered' liquids. Combining a magical extracted/filtered liquid with a mundane extracted/filtered liquid consistently yields 100 points. message: To get 100 value, always use the vial on a solid ingredient and the filter on a gas ingredient. Then, combine the resulting extracted and filtered items. The trick is that for 100 value, one of the combined items must have a 'magical' feature and the other must have a 'mundane' feature. If both are magical or both mundane, you'll only get 60.
